The mixed exercises provide comprehensive practice across all skills in this lesson. Problem types include:

* Solving quadratic equations using the Quadratic Formula, with and without rearrangement into standard form.
* Determining the number of [ x ]-intercepts of a related quadratic function by evaluating the discriminant.
* Solving geometry word problems involving rectangles, cylinders, and frames.
* Analyzing projectile motion and fireworks trajectories, including finding launch height, time to ground, maximum height, and times at a given altitude.
* Reasoning about parameter values (such as [ q ] or [ k ]) that yield a specific number of solutions.
